obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (28496)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and duration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28496&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Requisitioning and Acquisition`
  line `of Immovable Property Act, 1952.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (3) omitted by Act 1 of 1970, s. 2 (w.e.f. 11-3-1970).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (28497)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28497&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "award" means any award of an arbitrator made under section 8;`
  line
  line `(b) "competent authority" means any person or authority authorised by the Central Government,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, to perform the functions of the competent authority under this`
  line `Act for such area as may be specified in the notification;`
  line
  line `(c) "landlord" means any person who for the time being is receiving or is entitled to receive, the`
  line `rent of any premises, whether on his own account, or on account or on behalf or for the benefit, of`
  line `any other person or as a trustee, guardian or receiver for any other person, or who would so receive`
  line `the rent or be entitled to receive the rent if the premises were let to a tenant;`
  line
  line `(d) the expression "person interested", in relation to any property, includes all persons claiming,`
  line `or entitled to claim, an interest in the compensation payable on account of the requisitioning or`
  line `acquisition of that property under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "premises" means any building or part of a building and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the garden, grounds and outhouses, if any, appertaining to such building or part of a`
  line building;
  line
  line `(ii) any fittings affixed to such building or part of a building for the more beneficial`
  line `enjoyment thereof;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "property" means immovable property of every kind and includes any rights in or over such`
  line property;
  line
  line `(h) "tenant" means any person by whom or on whose account rent is payable for any premises`
  line `and includes such sub-tenants and other persons as have derived title under the tenant under any law`
  line `for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (28498)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to requisition immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28498&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the competent authority is of opinion that`
  line `any property is needed or likely to be needed for any public purpose, being a purpose of the Union, and`
  line `that the property should be requisitioned, the competent authority--`
  line
  line `(a) shall call upon the owner or any other person who may be in possession of the property by`
  line `notice in writing (specifying therein the purpose of the requisition) to show cause, within fifteen days`
  line `of the date of the service of such notice on him, why the property should not be requisitioned; and`
  line
  line `(b) may, by order, direct that neither the owner of the property nor any other person shall, without`
  line `permission of the competent authority, dispose of, or structurally alter, the property or let it out to a`
  line `tenant until the expiry of such period, not exceeding two months, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) If, after considering the cause, if any, shown by any person interested in the property or in`
  line `possession thereof, the competent authority is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do, it may,`
  line `by order in writing, requisition the property and may make such further orders as appear to it to be`
  line `necessary or expedient in connection with the requisitioning:`
  line
  line `Provided that no property or part thereof--`
  line
  line `(a) which is bona fide used by the owner thereof as the residence of himself or his family, or`
  line
  line `(b) which is exclusively used either for religious worship by the public or as a school, hospital,`
  line `public library or an orphanage or for the purpose of accommodation of persons connected with the`
  line `management of such place of worship or such school, hospital, library or orphanage,`
  line
  line `shall be requisitioned:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the requisitioned property consists of premises which are being used as a`
  line `residence by a tenant for not less than two months immediately preceding the date of the service of notice`
  line `under sub-section (1), the competent authority shall provide such tenant with alternative accommodation`
  line `which, in its opinion, is suitable.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (28499)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Power to take possession of requisitioned property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28499&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property has been`
  line `requisitioned under section 3, the competent authority may, by notice in writing, order the owner as well`
  line `as any other person who may be in possession of the property to surrender or deliver possession thereof to`
  line `the competent authority or any person duly authorised by it in this behalf within thirty days of the service`
  line `of the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person refuses or fails to comply with an order made under sub-section (1), the competent`
  line `authority may take possession of the property and may, for that purpose, use such force as may be`
  line necessary.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (28500)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Rights over requisitioned property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28500&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) All property requisitioned under section 3, shall be used`
  line `for such purposes as may be mentioned in the notice of requisition.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any premises are requisitioned under section 3, the competent authority may order the`
  line `landlord to execute such repairs as may be necessary and are usually made by landlords in that locality`
  line `and as may be specified in the notice, within such reasonable time as may be mentioned therein, and if the`
  line `landlord fails to execute any repairs in pursuance of such order, the competent authority may cause the`
  line `repairs specified in the order to be executed at the expense of the landlord and the cost thereof may,`
  line `without prejudice to any other mode of recovery, be deducted from the compensation payable to the`
  line landlord.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (28501)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Release from requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28501&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may at any time release from`
  line `requisition any property requisitioned under this Act and shall, as far as possible, restore the property in`
  line `as good a condition as it was when possession thereof was taken subject only to the changes caused by`
  line `reasonable wear and tear and irresistible force:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the purposes for which any requisitioned property was being used cease to exist,`
  line `the Central Government shall, unless the property is acquired under section 7, release that property, as`
  line `soon as may be, from requisition.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Central Government shall release`
  line `from requisition,--`
  line
  line `(a) any property requisitioned or deemed to be requisitioned under this Act before the`
  line `commencement of the Requisitioning and Acquisition of Immovable Property (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1970 (1 of 1970), on or before the expiry of a period of ^2[seventeen years] from such`
  line commencement;
  line
  line `(b) any property requisitioned under this Act after such commencement, on or before the expiry`
  line `of a period of ^2[seventeen years] from the date on which possession of such property was surrendered`
  line `or delivered to, or taken by, the competent authority under section 4,`
  line
  line `unless such property is acquired under section 7 within the period of ^2[seventeen years] aforesaid].`
  line
  line `(2) Where any property is to be released from requisition, ^4[under sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A)]`
  line `the competent authority may, after such inquiry, if any, as it may in any case consider necessary to make`
  line `or cause to be made, specify by order in writing the person to whom possession of the property shall be`
  line `given and such possession shall, as far as practicable, be given to the person from whom possession was`
  line `taken at the time of the requisition or to the successors-in-interest of such person.`
  line
  line `(3) The delivery of possession of the property to the person specified in an order under`
  line `sub-section (2) shall be a full discharge of the Central Government from all liability in respect of the`
  line `property, but shall not prejudice any rights in respect of the property which any other person may be`
  line `entitled by due process of law to enforce against the person to whom possession of the property is given.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any person to whom possession of any requisitioned property is to be given is not found`
  line `and has no agent or other person empowered to accept delivery on his behalf, the competent authority`
  line `shall cause a notice declaring that the property is released from requisition to be affixed on some`
  line `conspicuous part of the property and shall also publish the notice in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) When a notice referred to in sub-section (4) is published in the Official Gazette, the property`
  line `specified in such notice shall cease to be subject to requisition on and from the date of such publication`
  line `and shall be deemed to have been delivered to the person entitled to possession thereof and the Central`
  line `Government shall not be liable for any compensation or other claim in respect of the property for any`
  line `period after the said date.`
  line
  line `(6) Where any property requisitioned under this Act or any material part thereof is wholly destroyed`
  line `or rendered substantially and permanently unfit for the purpose for which it was requisitioned by reason`
  line `of fire, earthquake, tempest, flood or violence of any army or of a mob or other irresistible force, the`
  line `requisition shall, at the option of the Central Government, be void:`
  line
  line `Provided that the benefit of this sub-section shall not be available to the Central Government where`
  line `the injury to such property is caused by any wrongful act or default of that Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 1 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 11-3-1970).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 20 of 1985, s. 2, for "fifteen years" (w.e.f. 8-3-1985).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 1 of 1970, s. 3 (w.e.f. 11-3-1970).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (28502)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to acquire requisitioned property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 21 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 14-3-1952).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28502&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property is subject to requisition, the`
  line `Central Government may, if it is of opinion that it is necessary to acquire the property for a public`
  line `purpose, at any time acquire such property by publishing in the Official Gazette a notice to the effect that`
  line `the Central Government has decided to acquire the property in pursuance of this section:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing such notice, the Central Government shall call upon the owner of, or any`
  line `other person who, in the opinion of the Central Government, may be interested in, such property to show`
  line `cause why the property should not be acquired; and after considering the cause, if any, shown by any`
  line `person interested in the property and after giving the parties an opportunity of being heard, the Central`
  line `Government may pass such orders as it deems fit.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(1A) Notwithstanding any judgment or order by a court or any other authority, setting aside a notice`
  line `under sub-section (1) on the ground that the owner or any other person who may be interested in the`
  line `property was not given adequate opportunity to show cause or personal hearing, the Central Government`
  line `may re-issue the notice to the owner or such other person interested in the property, for the purpose of`
  line `giving opportunity of being heard:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a notice is re-issued, the owner or such other person interested in the property`
  line `shall be entitled to the same annual rate of interest, prevalent at any relevant time on the domestic fixed`
  line `deposit offered by the State Bank of India, as defined under clause (g) of section 2 of the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), on the compensation payable under this Act, from the date of publication of`
  line `the first notice, till the final payment of the compensation under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any enhanced compensation with or without interest awarded by the court or`
  line `other authority, before the date of commencement of the Requisitioning and Acquisition of Immovable`
  line `Property (Amendment) Act, 2018, shall be subject to the re-issuance of a notice under this sub-section`
  line `and shall be applicable only to the cases of land being acquired for national security and defence purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in the cases, where the final award under this Act has been made any compensation`
  line `thereof has been accepted by the owner or such other person interested in the property, before the`
  line `commencement of the Requisitioning and Acquisition of the immovable Property (Amendment) Act,`
  line `2018, shall not be reopened.]`
  line
  line `(2) When a notice as aforesaid is published in the Official Gazette, the requisitioned property shall, on`
  line `and from the beginning of the day on which the notice is so published, vest absolutely in the Central`
  line `Government free from all encumbrances and the period of requisition of such property shall end.`
  line
  line `(3) No property shall be acquired under this section except in the following circumstances, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Where any works have, during the period of requisition, been constructed on, in or over, the`
  line `property wholly or partially at the expense of the Central Government and the Government decides`
  line `that the value of, or the right to use, such works should be secured or preserved for the purposes of`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the cost of restoring the property to its condition at the time of its requisition would, in`
  line `the determination of the Central Government, be excessive and the owner declines to accept release`
  line `from requisition of the property without payment of compensation for so restoring the property.`
  line
  line `(4) Any decision or determination of the Central Government under sub-section (3) shall be final and`
  line `shall not be called in question in any Court.`
  line
  line `(5) For the purposes of clause (a) of sub-section (3) works includes buildings, structures and`
  line `improvements of every description.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (28503)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Principles and method of determining compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28503&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any property is requisitioned`
  line `or acquired under this Act, there shall be paid compensation the amount of which shall be determined in`
  line `the manner and in accordance with the principles hereinafter set out, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the amount of compensation can be fixed by agreement, it shall be paid in accordance`
  line `with such agreement;`
  line
  line `(b) where no such agreement can be reached, the Central Government shall appoint as arbitrator a`
  line `person who is, or has been, or is qualified for appointment as, a Judge of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(c) the Central Government may, in any particular case, nominate a person having expert`
  line `knowledge as to the nature of the property requisitioned or acquired to assist the arbitrator and where`
  line `such nomination is made, the person to be compensated may also nominate an assessor for the same`
  line purpose;
  line
  line `(d) at the commencement of the proceedings before the arbitrator, the Central Government and`
  line `the person to be compensated shall state what in their respective opinion is a fair amount of`
  line compensation;
  line
  line `(e) the arbitrator shall, after hearing the dispute, make an award determining the amount of compensation`
  line `which appears to him to be just and specifying the person or persons to whom such`
  line `compensation shall be paid; and in making the award, he shall have regard to the circumstances of`
  line `each case and the provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3), so far as they are applicable;`
  line
  line `(f) where there is any dispute as to the person or persons who are entitled to the compensation, the`
  line `arbitrator shall decide such dispute and if the arbitrator finds that more persons than one are entitled`
  line `to compensation, he shall apportion the amount thereof amongst such persons;`
  line
  line `(g) nothing in the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940) shall apply to arbitrations under this section.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^1[The amount of compensation payable for the requisitioning of any property shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of sub-sections (2A) and (2B), consist of--]`
  line
  line `(a) a recurring payment, in respect of the period of requisition, of a sum equal to the rent which`
  line `would have been payable for the use and occupation of the property, if it had been taken on lease for`
  line `that period; and`
  line
  line `(b) such sum or sums, if any, as may be found necessary to compensate the person interested for`
  line `all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) pecuniary loss due to requisitioning;`
  line
  line `(ii) expenses on account of vacating the requisitioned premises;`
  line
  line `(iii) expenses on account of reoccupying the premises upon release from requisition; and`
  line
  line `(iv) damages (other than normal wear and tear) caused to the property during the period of`
  line `requisition, including the expenses that may have to be incurred for restoring the property to the`
  line `condition in which it was at the time of requisition.`
  line
  line `^2[(2A) The recurring payment, referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2), in respect of any property`
  line `shall, unless the property is sooner released from requisition under section 6 or acquired under section 7,`
  line `be revised in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2B)--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where such property has been subject to requisition under this Act for the period of`
  line `five years or a longer period immediately preceding the commencement of the Requisitioning and`
  line `Acquisition of Immovable Property (Amendment) Act, 1975--`
  line
  line `(i) first with effect from the date of such commencement, and`
  line
  line `^3[(ii) secondly with effect from the expiry of five years, and thirdly with effect from the`
  line `expiry of ten years, from such commencement;]]`
  line
  line `(b) in a case where such property has been subject to requisition under this Act immediately`
  line `before such commencement for a period shorter than five years and the maximum period within`
  line `which such property shall, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1A) of section 6, be`
  line `released from requisition or acquired, extends beyond five years from such commencement,--`
  line
  line `(i) first with effect from the date of expiry of five years from the date on which possession of`
  line `such property has been surrendered or delivered to, or taken by, the competent authority under`
  line `section 4, and`
  line
  line `^3[(ii) secondly with effect from the date of expiry of five years, and thirdly with effect from`
  line `the date of expiry of ten years, from the date on which the revision made under sub-clause (i)`
  line `takes effect;]`
  line
  line `^4[(c) in any other case,--`
  line
  line `(i) first with effect from the date of expiry of five years from the date on which possession of`
  line `such property has been surrendered or delivered to, or taken by, the competent authority under`
  line `section 4, and`
  line
  line `^5[(ii) secondly with effect from the date of expiry of five years, and thirdly with effect from`
  line `the date of expiry of ten years, from the date on which the revision under sub-clause (i) takes`
  line effect.]]
  line
  line `(2B) The recurring payment in respect of any property shall be revised by re-determining`
  line `such payment in the manner and in accordance with the principles set out in sub-section (1), read with`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (2), as if such property had been requisitioned under this Act on the date with`
  line `effect from which the revision has to be made under sub-section (2A).]`
  line
  line `^6[(3) The compensation payable for the acquisition of any property under section 7 shall be the price`
  line `which the requisitioned property would have fetched in the open market, if it had remained in the same`
  line `condition as it was at the time of requisitioning and been sold on the date of acquisition.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1975, s. 3, for "The amount of compensation payable for the requisitioning of any property shall`
  line `consisit of--" (w.e.f. 1-3-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 2 of 1975, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-3-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 35 of 1980, s. 3, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 7-3-1980).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 7-3-1980).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 20 of 1985, s. 3, for sub-clause (ii) (w.e.f. 8-3-1985).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 31 of 1968, s. 2, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-8-1968).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (28504)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28504&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The amount of compensation payable under an award shall, subject`
  line `to any rules made under this Act, be paid by the competent authority to the person or persons entitled`
  line `thereto in such manner and within such time as may be specified in the award.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (28505)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Appeals from orders of requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28505&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of requisition`
  line `made by the competent authority under sub-section (2) of section 3 may, within twenty-one days from the`
  line `date of service of the order, prefer an appeal to the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `twenty-one days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the`
  line `appeal in time.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Central Government may, after calling for a`
  line `report from the competent authority and giving an opportunity to the parties of being heard and after`
  line `making such further inquiry, if any, as may be necessary, pass such orders as it thinks fit and the order of`
  line `the Central Government shall be final.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an appeal is preferred under sub-section (1), the Central Government may stay the`
  line `enforcement of the order of the competent authority for such period and on such conditions as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (28506)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Appeals from awards in respect of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28506&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an award of the`
  line `arbitrator made under section 8 may, within thirty days from the dale of such award, prefer an appeal to`
  line `the High Court within whose jurisdiction the requisitioned or acquired property is situate:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of thirty`
  line `days, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the appeal in time.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (28507)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Competent authority and arbitrator to have certain powers of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28507&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The competent`
  line `authority and the arbitrator appointed under section 8, while holding an inquiry or, as the case may be,`
  line `arbitration proceedings under this Act, shall have all the powers of a civil court, while trying a suit, under`
  line `the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (28508)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28508&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or the competent authority may, with a`
  line `view to carrying out the purposes of section 3 or section 6, or section 7, or section 8, by order require any`
  line `person to furnish to such officer, as may be specified in the order, such information in his possession as`
  line `may be specified relating to any property which is requisitioned or acquired, or intended to be`
  line `requisitioned or acquired, under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (28509)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to enter and inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28509&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority or any officer, empowered in this behalf`
  line `by such authority by general or special order, may enter and inspect any property for the purposes of`
  line `determining whether, and if so, in what manner, an order under this Act should be made in relation to`
  line `such property or with a view to securing compliance with an order made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (28510)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Service of notice and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28510&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section and any rules that`
  line `may be made under this Act, every notice or order issued or made under this Act shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of any notice or order of a general nature or affecting a class of persons, be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any notice or order affecting an individual, corporation or firm be served in the`
  line `manner provided for the service of summons in Rule 2 of Order XXIX or Rule 3 of Order XXX, as`
  line `the case may be, in the First Schedule of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908); and`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of any notice or order affecting an individual person (not being a corporation or`
  line `firm), be served on such person--`
  line
  line `(i) by delivering or tendering it to that person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it cannot be so delivered or tendered, by delivering or tendering it to any officer of such`
  line `person or any adult male member of the family of such person, or by affixing a copy thereof on`
  line `the outer door or on some conspicuous part of the premises in which that person is known to have`
  line `last resided or carried on business or personally worked for gain; or failing service by these`
  line means;
  line
  line `(iii) by post.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the ownership of the property is in dispute or where the persons interested in the property`
  line `are not readily traceable and the notice or order cannot be served without undue delay, the notice or order`
  line `may be served by publishing it in the Official Gazette, and where possible, by affixing a copy thereof on`
  line `any conspicuous part of the property to which it relates.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (28511)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Easement not to be disturbed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28511&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No person interested in any property requisitioned or acquired`
  line `under this Act shall, without the previous written consent of the competent authority or except for the`
  line `purposes of effecting repairs or complying with a municipal requirement, wilfully disturb any`
  line `convenience or easement attached to such property or remove, destroy or render unserviceable anything`
  line `provided for permanent use therewith or discontinue or cause to be discontinued any supply or service`
  line `provided for the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (28512)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28512&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the powers exercisable by it ^1*** under this Act shall, in such circumstances and under such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercisable also by an officer subordinate to`
  line `that Government or ^2[by the State Government or by an officer subordinate to the State Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) All notifications issued under sub-section (1) shall be laid, as soon as may be, before Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "by or" omitted by Act 42 of 1953, s. 4 and the Third Schedule (w.e.f. 23-12-1953).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4 and the Third Schedule, ibid., for "the State Government" (w.e.f. 23-12-1953).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (28513)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28513&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance`
  line `of this Act or any order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the competent`
  line `authority for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (28514)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28514&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no civil`
  line `court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the competent authority or arbitrator is`
  line `empowered by or under this Act to determine, and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other`
  line `authority in respect of any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (28515)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Penalty for offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28515&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act, or any rule made`
  line `thereunder, or any order made or direction given under this Act, or obstructs the lawful exercise of any`
  line `power conferred by or under this Act, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (28516)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Certain persons to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28516&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority, every arbitrator and every`
  line `officer empowered by the Central Government or the competent authority, while exercising any power or`
  line `performing any duty under this Act, shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of`
  line `section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)..`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (28517)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 35 of 1980, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 5-4-1980).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28517&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the competent authority in making inquiries under section 3`
  line `or section 6;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed in arbitration proceedings and appeals under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) the principles to be followed in determining the amount of compensation and method of`
  line `payment of such compensation;`
  line
  line `(d) the principles to be followed in apportioning the cost of proceedings before the arbitrator and`
  line `on appeal under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of service of notices and orders;`
  line
  line `(f) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (28518)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Validation of certain requisitions and acquisitions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28518&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) All immovable property which`
  line `purports to have been requisitioned by a State Government for any public purpose, being a purpose of the`
  line `Union, under any Provincial or State Act and which, immediately before the 25th day of January, 1952,`
  line `was used or occupied by the Central Government or by an officer or authority subordinate to that`
  line `Government shall, as from that date, be deemed to be property duly requisitioned under section 3 of this`
  line `Act, and every such requisition shall, notwithstanding any judgment, decree or order of any Court, be`
  line `deemed always to have been valid as if this Act had been in force on and from the date of the requisition`
  line `and the requisition had been duly made by a competent authority under this Act, and all the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that all agreements and awards for the payment of compensation in respect of any such`
  line `property for any period of requisition before the 25th day of January, 1952 and in force immediately`
  line `before that date shall be valid and shall be deemed always to have been valid and shall continue to be in`
  line `force and shall apply to the payment of compensation in respect of that property for any period of`
  line `requisition after that date.`
  line
  line `(2) Every acquisition of immovable property purporting to have been made before the`
  line `commencement of this Act by a State Government for any public purpose, being a purpose of the Union,`
  line `under any enactment for the time being in force in that State and which, immediately before such`
  line `commencement, was used or occupied by the Central Government or by an officer or authority`
  line `subordinate to that Government shall, notwithstanding any defect in, or invalidity of, the enactment or`
  line `order under which the acquisition was made, be deemed for all purposes to have been validly made as if`
  line `the provisions of the said enactment or order had been included and enacted in this section and this`
  line `section had been in force on and from the date of the acquisition.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (28519)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Repeals and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28519&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Requisitioned Land (Continuance of Powers)`
  line `Act, 1947 (17 of 1947), the Delhi Premises (Requisition and Eviction) Act, 1947 (49 of 1947), and the`
  line `Requisitioning and Acquisition of Immovable Property Ordinance, 1952 (3 of 1952), are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any property which immediately before such`
  line `repeal was subject to requisition under the provisions of either of the said Acts or the said Ordinance`
  line `shall, on the commencement of this Act, be deemed to be property requisitioned under section 3 of this`
  line `Act, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that--`
  line
  line `(a) all agreements and awards for the payment of compensation in respect of any such property`
  line `for any period of requisition before the commencement of this Act and in force immediately before`
  line `such commencement, shall continue to be in force and shall apply to the payment of compensation in`
  line `respect of that property for any period of requisition after such commencement;`
  line
  line `(b) anything done or any action taken (including any orders, notifications or rules made or issued)`
  line `in exercise of the powers conferred by or under either of the said Acts or the said Ordinance shall, in`
  line `so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken in`
  line `the exercise of the powers conferred by or under this Act as if this Act was in force on the day in`
  line `which such thing was done or action was taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (28520)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Special provision as to certain requisitions under Act 51 of 1962.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1968, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-1-1968).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28520&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[25. Special provision as to certain requisitions under Act 51 of 1962.--(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, any immovable property requisitioned by the Central Government or by`
  line `any officer or authority to whom powers in this behalf have been delegated by that Government, under`
  line `the Defence of India Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), and the rules made thereunder (including any immovable`
  line `property deemed to have been requisitioned under the said Act) which has not been released from such`
  line `requisition before the 10th January, 1968, shall, as from that date, be deemed to have been requisitioned`
  line `by the competent authority under the provisions of this Act for the purpose for which such property was`
  line `held immediately before the said date and all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that`
  line
  line `(a) all determinations, agreements and awards for the payment of compensation in respect of any`
  line `such property for any period of requisition before the said date and in force immediately before the`
  line `said date, shall continue to be in force and shall apply to the payment of compensation in respect of`
  line `that property for any period of requisition as from the said date;`
  line
  line `(b) anything done or any action taken (including any orders, notifications or rules made or issued)`
  line `by the Central Government or by any officer or authority to whom powers in this behalf have been`
  line `delegated by that Government, in exercise of the powers conferred by or under Chapter VI of the`
  line `Defence of India Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act, be deemed to have been done or taken in the exercise of the powers conferred by or under`
  line `this Act as if this section was in force on the date on which such thing was done or action was taken.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), the provisions of the Defence of India`
  line `Act, 1962 (51 of 1962), and the rules made thereunder, in so far as those provisions relate to the`
  line `requisitioning of any such immovable property as is referred to in sub-section (1), shall, as from the 10th`
  line `January, 1968, cease to operate except as respects things done or omitted to be done before such cesser`
  line `and section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply upon such cesser of operation as`
  line `if such cesser were a repeal of an enactment by a Central Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (28521)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Special provision as to certain requisitions under Act 42 of 1971.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1977, s. 2 (w.e.f. 21-3-1977).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394&sectionId=28521&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00032_195230_1517807328394
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Special provision as to certain requisitions under Act 42 of 1971.--(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, any immovable property requisitioned or purported to have been`
  line `requisitioned by the Central Government or by any officer or authority to whom powers in this behalf`
  line `have been delegated by that Government, under the Defence of India Act, 1971 (42 of 1971), and the`
  line `rules made thereunder (including any immovable property deemed to have been requisitioned under the`
  line `said Act), which has not been released from such requisition before the appointed day, shall,--`
  line
  line `(i) if such property was requisitioned on or before the 21st day of March, 1977, as from that date,`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) if such property was requisitioned at any time after such date, as from the date of its`
  line requisition,
  line
  line `be deemed to have been requisitioned by the competent authority under the provisions of this Act for the`
  line `purpose for which such property was held immediately before the appointed day and all the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that in determining the compensation payable under this Act in respect of any property so`
  line `deemed to have been requisitioned under this Act, the sum or sums, if any, as may be found necessary to`
  line `compensate the person interested for all or any of the matters specified in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 8 shall be reduced by the sum or sums, if any, paid or payable in respect of such matter or matters`
  line `as compensation in respect of such property under the Defence of India Act, 1971 (42 of 1971), and the`
  line `rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), the provisions of the Defence of India`
  line `Act, 1971 (42 of 1971), and the rules made thereunder, in so far as those provisions relate to the`
  line `requisitioning of any such immovable property as is referred to in sub-section (1), shall, as from the 21st`
  line `March, 1977, cease to operate except as respects things done or omitted to be done before such cesser and`
  line `section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply upon such cesser of operation as if`
  line `such cesser were a repeal of an enactment by a Central Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this section "appointed day" means the 23rd September, 1977.]`
